Key Match Events: The New York Mets defeated the Washington Nationals 10-1 last night.
The Washington Nationals had the New York Mets starter Tylor Megill on the ropes in the third inning, putting runners on first and third with no outs, but they could score only one run.
James Wood hit into a fielder’s choice, allowing Jacob Young to score the only game run for Washington.
The Nationals offense struggled as the team was 0-for-5 with runners in scoring position.
Pre-Game Insights: Pitching Matchup: LHP DJ Herz (4-7; 3.70 ERA) vs. LHP Jose Quintana (9-9; 3.91 ERA)
The Washington Nationals finish up their three game series against the New York Mets tonight.
